description:
IT Service Delivery Junior Engineer**Location****:** Sweden, Gävle

**Job category****:** Information Technology (IT)

**Language****:** English, Swedish


Are you at the beginning of your IT career and want to work in an international environment where technology meets customer service? We are currently looking for an engaged and technically interested Junior IT Technician to join our office in Gävle!


Join us as a IT Service Delivery Junior Engineer!


In this role, you will:

* Provide first-class support for desktops, laptops, printers, and other peripherals;
* Handle and resolve cases through our ticketing system (ServiceNow) within defined timeframes (SLA);
* Perform installations, configurations, and system updates, as well as routine equipment checks;
* Carry out basic network troubleshooting (TCP/IP) and ensure compliance with our security standards and policies;
* Ensure that IT assets, configurations, and user guides are properly documented;
* Work closely with central IT teams and external vendors to resolve more complex issues and manage warranty cases or outages.


What’s in it for YOU!

* An exciting full-time position with immediate start;
* Opportunity to grow alongside experienced specialists in a company that values personal development and teamwork;
* A dynamic workplace focused on collaboration and support;
* Opportunity to work with modern tools and international processes;
* Benefits according to Transcom’s policy, such as wellness allowance and employee discounts.


To be successful in this role, the following is needed:

* Basic technical skills and understanding of computer hardware, Windows environments, and software installations;
* Basic understanding of networking (TCP/IP, DNS, and DHCP);
* Good proficiency in Swedish and English, as the role involves contact with international colleagues;
* A solution-oriented mindset and the ability to explain technical solutions in a simple way to non-technical users;
* Previous experience with ticketing systems or customer service environments is considered meritorious.


What Life at Transcom is like! At Transcom, we’re relentlessly committed. To our clients and each other. Every day, someone starts their journey with Transcom. Taking the potential they have today and turning it into skills for the future. Getting recognized for working hard, being a team player, and supporting others. Championing positive, lasting change in their teams and communities. That’s just how we are at Transcom. Here we care and root for each other. You’re included, just as you are, from day one. And with the right mindset, there’s no end to how far we can go together.
